                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At its meeting held on March 4, 1954, the National Security Council considered
                    and adopted the draft statement of policy contained in <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5409, “United States Policy Toward South Asia,” dated February
                    19, 1954, subject to certain alterations. On March 6, President <persName
                        corresp="#p_E1">Eisenhower</persName> approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5409 as amended. Section D of <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5409 deals specifically with Afghanistan.</p>
                <p>For texts of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5409, Gleasion’s memorandum
                    (drawn up March 5) of the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> discussion on
                    March 4, and Section D of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5409, see pages
                    1089, 1126, and 1151, respectively.</p>
            </div>
